    "message_2": "To find the value of y at x = 2.5 using Lagrange interpolation, we will use the formula:\n\ny(x) = L(x) = Σ [Li(x) * yi]\n\nwhere Li(x) = Π [(x - xj) / (xi - xj)] for j ≠ i\n\nGiven data points: (0, 0), (1, 3), (2, 12), (3, 27), (4, 48)\n\nLet's calculate the Lagrange polynomials L0(x), L1(x), L2(x), L3(x), and L4(x):\n\nL0(x) = [(x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)] / [(0 - 1) * (0 - 2) * (0 - 3) * (0 - 4)] = (x^4 - 10x^3 + 35x^2 - 50x + 24) / 24\n\nL1(x) = [(x - 0) * (x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)] / [(1 - 0) * (1 - 2) * (1 - 3) * (1 - 4)] = (x^4 - 9x^3 + 26x^2 - 24x) / -6\n\nL2(x) = [(x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)] / [(2 - 0) * (2 - 1) * (2 - 3) * (2 - 4)] = (x^4 - 8x^3 + 19x^2 - 16x) / 12\n\nL3(x) = [(x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 4)] / [(3 - 0) * (3 - 1) * (3 - 2) * (3 - 4)] = (x^4 - 7x^3 + 14x^2 - 8x) / -6\n\nL4(x) = [(x - 0) * (x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3)] / [(4 - 0) * (4 - 1) * (4 - 2) * (4 - 3)] = (x^4 - 6x^3 + 11x^2 - 6x) / 24\n\nNow, let's calculate y(2.5) using the Lagrange interpolation formula:\n\ny(2.5) = L0(2.5) * y0 + L1(2.5) * y1 + L2(2.5) * y2 + L3(2.5) * y3 + L4(2.5) * y4\n\ny(2.5) = L0(2.5) * 0 + L1(2.5) * 3 + L2(2.5) * 12 + L3(2.5) * 27 + L4(2.5) * 48\n\ny(2.5) = (-0.25) * 3 + 2.25 * 12 + (-1.5) * 27 + 1.25 * 48\n\ny(2.5) = -0.75 + 27 - 40.5 + 60\n\ny(2.5) = 46.75\n\nSo, the value of y at x = 2.5 based on Lagrange interpolation is 46.75."
